---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'bupa-global', text: 'Bupa Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'allianz-care', text: 'Allianz Care', level: 2 },
  { id: 'condition-coverage', text: 'Common Conditions Covered', level: 2 },
  { id: 'medication', text: 'Medication Coverage', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Chronic Conditions Guide', href: '/guides/chronic-conditions-coverage' },
  { title: 'Medications Abroad', href: '/guides/medications-abroad' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Chronic Condition Approach', cigna: 'Strict exclusions', bupa: 'Case-by-case', allianz: 'Most flexible' },
  { feature: 'Diabetes (controlled)', cigna: 'Often excluded', bupa: 'May cover', allianz: 'Often covered' },
  { feature: 'Hypertension', cigna: 'Usually covered', bupa: 'Usually covered', allianz: 'Usually covered' },
  { feature: 'Asthma', cigna: 'Usually covered', bupa: 'Usually covered', allianz: 'Usually covered' },
  { feature: 'Thyroid Conditions', cigna: 'Usually covered', bupa: 'Usually covered', allianz: 'Usually covered' },
  { feature: 'Heart Disease History', cigna: 'Often excluded', bupa: 'Case-by-case', allianz: 'May cover' },
  { feature: 'Medication Coverage', cigna: 'Excellent', bupa: 'Excellent', allianz: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Best For', cigna: 'Minor conditions', bupa: 'Moderate conditions', allianz: 'Complex conditions' },
];

const conditionColumns = [
  { key: 'condition', header: 'Condition' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz' },
];

const conditionRows = [
  { condition: 'Type 2 Diabetes (controlled)', cigna: 'Often excluded', bupa: 'May cover with loading', allianz: 'Often covered' },
  { condition: 'Hypertension (stable)', cigna: 'Usually covered', bupa: 'Usually covered', allianz: 'Usually covered' },
  { condition: 'Asthma (mild/moderate)', cigna: 'Usually covered', bupa: 'Usually covered', allianz: 'Usually covered' },
  { condition: 'Hypothyroidism', cigna: 'Usually covered', bupa: 'Usually covered', allianz: 'Usually covered' },
  { condition: 'High Cholesterol', cigna: 'Usually covered', bupa: 'Usually covered', allianz: 'Usually covered' },
  { condition: 'Depression/Anxiety history', cigna: 'Usually excluded', bupa: 'Often excluded', allianz: 'May cover' },
  { condition: 'Heart Disease history', cigna: 'Often excluded', bupa: 'Case-by-case', allianz: 'May cover with wait' },
  { condition: 'Cancer (in remission)', cigna: 'Usually excluded', bupa: 'Waiting period', allianz: 'Waiting period' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna vs Bupa vs Allianz: Best Insurance for Chronic Conditions 2026"
  description="Compare how Cigna, Bupa, and Allianz handle chronic conditions like diabetes, hypertension, and heart disease. Which insurer is most likely to cover your existing conditions?"
  headline="Cigna vs Bupa vs Allianz: Chronic Condition Coverage Compared"
  subheadline="Living with diabetes, hypertension, or other chronic conditions? Here's which insurer is most likely to cover you—and how coverage works."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Most Flexible</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Most likely to cover chronic conditions. Moratorium option available. Best for diabetes, heart history.</p>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-purple-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Middle Ground</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Case-by-case underwriting. May cover with loading or waiting period. Good continuation options.</p>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Strictest</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Best service but strictest underwriting. Good for minor conditions only. Best coverage once accepted.</p>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    If you have chronic conditions, your insurer choice matters more than anything else. Allianz is most likely to cover existing conditions. Bupa takes a case-by-case approach. Cigna provides the best service but is strictest on pre-existing conditions.
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="cigna-global">Cigna Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Service</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Strict Underwriting</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Medication</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Cigna Global provides the best service and medication coverage once you're accepted—but they're strictest on chronic conditions at underwriting. Minor, well-controlled conditions may be fine; complex conditions are often permanently excluded.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Chronic condition handling:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Full medical underwriting required</li>
    <li>Minor conditions (hypertension, mild asthma) often covered</li>
    <li>Complex conditions (diabetes, heart history) often excluded</li>
    <li>Clear yes/no decisions (less negotiation than Bupa)</li>
    <li>Excellent medication coverage once accepted</li>
    <li>Best network for specialist access</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Those with minor, well-controlled conditions. People who prioritize service quality over underwriting flexibility. Anyone with conditions likely to be covered.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="bupa-global">Bupa Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Case-by-Case</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Premium Loading</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Lifetime Renewal</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Bupa Global takes a case-by-case approach. Instead of automatic exclusions, they review your specific situation. They may cover conditions with premium loading (higher cost) or waiting periods rather than excluding outright. Lifetime renewal protects you once accepted.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Chronic condition handling:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Individual case-by-case review</li>
    <li>May cover with premium loading (10-50% extra)</li>
    <li>May cover with waiting period (12-24 months)</li>
    <li>More negotiation possible than Cigna</li>
    <li>Lifetime renewal once accepted</li>
    <li>No-claims discount helps offset loading</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Those with moderate chronic conditions. People willing to pay more for coverage. Anyone who values lifetime renewal protection.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/bupa-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="allianz-care">Allianz Care</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Most Flexible</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Moratorium Option</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Mental Health</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Allianz Care is the most accommodating for chronic conditions. Their moratorium underwriting option lets you skip medical questions—conditions excluded for 24 months, then covered if stable. They're also most likely to cover conditions that Cigna excludes.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Chronic condition handling:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Most flexible underwriting of the three</li>
    <li>Moratorium option: no medical questions, 24-month wait</li>
    <li>Full underwriting: more lenient than competitors</li>
    <li>Diabetes often covered (unlike Cigna)</li>
    <li>Mental health history treated more favorably</li>
    <li>Heart disease may be covered with waiting period</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Those with complex chronic conditions. Anyone declined by Cigna or Bupa. People who prefer the moratorium option.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/allianz-care" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Coverage for Your Conditions"
    description="Disclose your conditions upfront and get accurate quotes showing what's covered."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="condition-coverage">How Common Conditions Are Handled</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={conditionColumns} rows={conditionRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-2">
    *These are general patterns. Individual decisions depend on severity, control, and complete medical history.
  </p>

  <h3>What "Controlled" Means</h3>
  <p>
    For a condition to be considered "controlled" or "stable," insurers typically look for:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Regular monitoring (doctor visits, tests)</li>
    <li>Consistent medication compliance</li>
    <li>Numbers in acceptable range (A1c, blood pressure, etc.)</li>
    <li>No hospitalizations related to the condition</li>
    <li>No recent changes in treatment</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Documentation Matters</h3>
  <p>
    When applying with chronic conditions, provide:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Recent lab results (within 6 months)</li>
    <li>List of current medications and doses</li>
    <li>Letter from your doctor about condition status</li>
    <li>Treatment history and any complications</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="medication">Medication Coverage for Chronic Conditions</h2>

  <p>
    Once your condition is covered, medication coverage varies:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Best medication coverage—most drugs covered, easy refills, good network</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa:</strong> Excellent coverage—similar to Cigna, good for specialty drugs</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Good coverage—may have more limits on specialty medications</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Getting Medications Abroad</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Brand names may differ by country</li>
    <li>Some medications may not be available everywhere</li>
    <li>Bring documentation of your prescriptions</li>
    <li>Consider 90-day supplies when available</li>
    <li>International pharmacies can often source medications</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Allianz Care if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Have diabetes or heart disease history</li>
        <li>Have mental health history</li>
        <li>Have been declined elsewhere</li>
        <li>Prefer moratorium underwriting</li>
        <li>Have multiple chronic conditions</li>
        <li>Want the most flexible approach</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Bupa Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Have moderate, well-controlled conditions</li>
        <li>Are willing to pay premium loading for coverage</li>
        <li>Want lifetime renewal protection</li>
        <li>Value case-by-case consideration</li>
        <li>Have conditions that need negotiation</li>
        <li>Want no-claims discounts to offset loading</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Have minor, well-controlled conditions</li>
        <li>Are likely to pass underwriting</li>
        <li>Want the best service once accepted</li>
        <li>Prioritize medication coverage</li>
        <li>Need the largest specialist network</li>
        <li>Have conditions Cigna typically covers</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Should I disclose all my conditions?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, absolutely. Non-disclosure can void your policy when you need it most. Insurers can access medical records. It's always better to know upfront what's covered than to face a denied claim later.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I'm declined by all three?</h3>
  <p>
    Work with a specialist international insurance broker who can access niche markets. Consider local insurance in your destination country—some have guaranteed-issue options. Some conditions may require you to self-insure for that specific issue.
  </p>

  <h3>Can conditions become covered over time?</h3>
  <p>
    With Allianz's moratorium: yes, after 24 months symptom-free. With full underwriting: some insurers review exclusions after 2-5 years. Ask your insurer about their review policy—but don't count on it.
  </p>

  <h3>What about conditions that develop while I'm insured?</h3>
  <p>
    Conditions that develop after your policy starts are fully covered—they're not pre-existing. This is why getting insured while healthy is so valuable. Once you have a policy, new diagnoses are covered.
  </p>

  <h3>Is "well-controlled" good enough?</h3>
  <p>
    Depends on the condition and insurer. Well-controlled hypertension on medication is usually fine. Well-controlled diabetes on insulin still often gets excluded by Cigna. Allianz is most lenient about what "controlled" means.
  </p>

  <h3>Do chronic conditions affect premium?</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna: usually exclusion (not loading). Bupa: often loading (10-50% extra). Allianz: sometimes loading or waiting period. Loading means you pay more but the condition is covered—often worth it.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison provides general patterns. Every application is evaluated individually based on specific medical history. Get actual underwriting decisions before choosing your insurer.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
